title: Dr. Jekyll & Mr. Hyde - Best of Coast to Coast AM - 10/18/22

description:
George Noory and author Leslie Klinger discuss the 19th century century novel "The Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll & Mr. Hyde" by Robert Lewis Stevenson, the true meaning of the story about split personalities, and why it has remained relevant in popular culture like plays and movies nearly one hundred fifty years after it was first written.
